<h2>Usage</h2>
<p>Use timelines to draw a connection for the user between linear pieces of information.</p>
<p>Examples include:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Steps or stages of a process</li>
  <li>Sequential dates or outcomes</li>
</ul>

<h2>Timeline types</h2>
<p>Timelines use colours from your brand palette, displayed as outlined or filled. Counters can also be added where they correspond to the content. </p>
<p>Colour selection should take into considertation it’s contrast with the content background.</p>

<h2>When to avoid</h2>
<p>Do not use when content doesn’t come together in sequential or linear order, consider bullets points instead.</p>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p>All components are responsive and meet WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility guidelines.</p>